defaultTHE NATIONAL SITUATION REGARDING ONLINE SAFETY
defaultThe 
defaultCommittee will no doubt be aware of the many statistics published by Ofcom on the subject of children and safety online.  Therefore it is not necessary for me to go into too much detail regarding the national situation
default; however I must point out that it is 
defaultvery clear from data gathered that many parents in the UK, unlike myself and my wife, are relatively unaware of how 
defaultpotent
default the hidden dangers of the internet are.  While most parents acknowledge that there should be some form of parental control, many do n
defaultot view the potential dangers as particularly serious so are not pro-active in controlling their children’s use; therefore they allow their children to spend long periods online alone without supervision and without controlling software.  This key fact cou
defaultld have a serious negative impact on UK society in the future if it is not properly addressed now.  This is of great
default concern to me.  A few key Ofcom findings bear this out:
